import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Select only numeric columns from the DataFrame
numeric_df = df_processed.select_dtypes(include=['float64', 'int64'])

# Calculate the correlation matrix for the numeric columns
corr_matrix = numeric_df.corr()

# Plot the correlation heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.heatmap(corr_matrix, annot=True, fmt=".2f", cmap='coolwarm')
plt.title('Correlation Heatmap for Numeric Columns')
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from sklearn.feature_selection import SelectKBest, f_classif
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

# Load the fully processed data
df_processed = pd.read_csv('D02fully_processed_telco_data.csv')

# Drop non-numeric columns and the target variable 'Churn_Yes'
X = df_processed.drop(columns=['customerID', 'Churn_Yes'])
In[4]:
# Ensure all features are numeric
X = X.apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce')

# Handle any remaining NaN values (if any)
X = X.fillna(0)

# Example of PCA for dimensionality reduction
pca = PCA(n_components=3)
df_reduced = pca.fit_transform(X)

# Example of Feature Selection
selector = SelectKBest(f_classif, k=10)
df_selected = selector.fit_transform(X, df_processed['Churn_Yes'])

# Handling imbalanced dataset
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, df_processed['Churn_Yes'], test_size=0.3, random_state=42)
smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
X_res, y_res = smote.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)

# After resampling check the balance
print("After SMOTE, counts of label '1': {}".format(sum(y_res == 1)))
print("After SMOTE, counts of label '0': {}".format(sum(y_res == 0)))

Explanation of Each Visualization
Distribution of the Target Variable: Shows the balance of churned vs. non-churned customers.
Boxplot of Tenure by Churn: Compares the distribution of tenure across churn and non-churn customers.
Boxplot of Monthly Charges by Churn: Compares the distribution of monthly charges across churn and non-churn customers.
Pairplot of Selected Features: Visualizes pairwise relationships between selected features, colored by churn.
Heatmap of Correlations: Shows correlations between different features, helping to identify relationships.
Violin Plot of TotalCharges by Churn: Displays the distribution and density of total charges across churn and non-churn customers.
Histogram of Tenure: Shows the distribution of customer tenure.
Histogram of Monthly Charges: Shows the distribution of monthly charges.
Countplot of Internet Service Type: Visualizes the number of customers using fiber optic internet.
Barplot of Contract Type by Churn: Shows the proportion of customers with a one-year contract by churn status.
Swarmplot of Monthly Charges by Churn: Another visualization of monthly charges by churn status, using a swarm plot.
Jointplot of Tenure and Monthly Charges: Displays the joint distribution of tenure and monthly charges.
KDE Plot of Tenure by Churn: Shows the distribution of tenure for churned vs. non-churned customers using KDE plots.
3D Scatterplot of PCA Components: Visualizes the first three PCA components in 3D space, colored by churn status.
3D Scatterplot of Selected Features: Visualizes the top three selected features in 3D space, colored by churn status.
3D Scatterplot of Tenure, Monthly Charges, and Total Charges: A 3D scatterplot of key features against churn status.
